      <div class="msgContentFrame">I've not seen mention of this detail in any of the update info on lodestone, and I haven't actually seen this specific issue in all the complaints about bazaars and market wards. (Sorry if I missed it.) <br /> <br />But it's kind of ludicrous that in order to request items through my bazaar, I firstly need said item, AND to purchase multiple items I need atleast the same number of said item already... <br /> <br />If I am looking to buy something doesn't it sort of insinuate a lack of that item? <br /> <br />in it's current state requesting items only ideally works for shards/crystals and a few materials and only if have them already... why can't I set my retainer to request a weapon I am looking for at the price I am willing to pay? Or if I run out of lightning crystals to make thread why do I need to go find/buy more before I can seek them in my bazaar? <br /> <br />It's a very backward system right now.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="HTTP://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/top?cicuid=1897972" rel="external nofollow" title="lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/top?cicuid=1897972"><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/1800135.png" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /></a> <br />Retainer: Ferthmart <br />FFXI: Ferth - Cerbereus Nee Hades Nee Leviathan.</div></div>
